# Boltic Ecommerce — Project Memory

## What is this project?
Boltic is a Vietnam-focused online marketplace for power banks. It supports Vietnamese (vi) and English (en) locales, integrates local payment methods, and is deployed on Vercel.

- **Live URL**: https://boltic-pexx-f9d10167.vercel.app  
- **GitHub**: https://github.com/marcuslimpexx/boltic  
- **Local path**: `/Users/marcuslim/Boltic Ecommerce/boltic/`

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js **15.5.18** (App Router, Webpack — NOT Turbopack) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict mode) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui |
| i18n | next-intl v4 (`vi` + `en`) |
| Auth | NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js) — Credentials Provider + JWT |
| Forms | react-hook-form + Zod v4 |
| State | Zustand (cart) |
| ORM | Prisma 7.8.0 + PostgreSQL (`@prisma/adapter-pg`) |
| Email | Resend |
| Payment | VNPay (stub provider in dev/staging) |
| Deployment | Vercel (Node.js ≥20) |

---

## Critical Deployment Notes

- **Next.js must stay at 15.5.18** — v16+ uses Turbopack for prod builds which Vercel does not yet support (causes universal 404s).
- **No `middleware.ts`** — All attempts to use NextAuth or next-intl middleware caused `MIDDLEWARE_INVOCATION_FAILED` on Vercel's Edge Runtime. Locale is set via `setRequestLocale(locale)` in `app/[locale]/layout.tsx` instead.
- **`opengraph-image.tsx` uses `runtime = "nodejs"`** — Prisma/pg use `fs`, incompatible with Edge Runtime.
- **`prisma generate` runs in the `build` script** (not `postinstall`) so errors are visible in Vercel build logs.
- **`vercel.json`** must NOT include `nodeVersion` (invalid schema). Node version is pinned via `"engines": { "node": ">=20.0.0" }` in `package.json`.
- **ESLint** is ignored during builds (`eslint: { ignoreDuringBuilds: true }` in `next.config.ts`).
- **Vercel Deployment Protection** should be DISABLED for the project to be publicly accessible.

